    "Body": " Diversity and Inclusion Specialist Ropes & Gray - 3.7 Boston, MA Apply Now Job Details Full-timeEstimated: $70,000 - $92,000 a year Qualifications Microsoft Outlook Human Resources Microsoft Word Microsoft Office Organizational Skills Bachelor's Degree Full Job Description About Ropes & Gray Ropes & Gray LLP is a preeminent global law firm focused on providing the highest-quality advice on our clients\u2019 critical legal and business issues. Our global team of 2,500 talented professionals regularly helps clients meet high-stakes challenges, solve complex problems and achieve key goals. These colleagues work together across a global office network that includes offices in Boston, Chicago, Hong Kong, London, New York, San Francisco, Seoul, Shanghai, Silicon Valley, Tokyo and Washington, D.C. We are a contemporary firm that can bring more than 150 years of legal and institutional history to bear on the challenges clients face in today\u2019s 24/7 global business environment. Our collaborative approach gives our clients\u2014which include many of the world\u2019s most respected companies and institutions\u2014ready access to leading corporate, litigation, transactional and regulatory lawyers whose knowledge and experience span industries and geographies. With an international presence, we focus on a number of key industries, including private equity; asset management; life sciences and health care; investment banking; technology, media and telecommunications; and consumer and retail. Our clients include global industry leaders, financial institutions, investment firms, private equity firms, hospitals and health care organizations, educational institutions, and individuals. We have consistently been recognized for our leading practices in many areas, including private equity, M&A, finance, asset management, real estate, tax, antitrust, life sciences, health care, intellectual property, litigation & enforcement, privacy & cybersecurity, and business restructuring. Ropes & Gray is an equal opportunity employer. JOB SUMMARY: The Diversity and Inclusion Specialist (\u201cthe specialist\u201d) will work closely with the Director of Diversity and Inclusion, and collaborate with the Attorney Talent team, to assist in all aspects of supporting the firm\u2019s diversity and inclusion efforts, including efforts related to attorney development and legal recruiting. The specialist will support affinity forum activities by providing support to the forums\u2019 co-chairs, coordinating and planning events and other programming. The specialist will also serve as a liaison to various business support departments to facilitate the implementation of various projects. ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS: Facilitate affinity group activities, including bi-monthly meetings, celebratory events and programs, related summer program activities and events, and the Annual Trimmier Scholars Reception and Dinner. Support legal recruiting efforts aimed at firm\u2019s diversity and inclusion goals, including coordinating the diversity outreach team and the Roscoe Trimmier Jr. Scholarship Award program. Update and maintain affinity forum distribution lists and mentoring circles. Coordinate and act as the point of contact for events, including creating/sending invitations, scheduling, moderating programs, acting as a liaison with Conference Services, and collecting and compiling feedback. Provide on-site support of various internal and external events. Serve as the point of contact for diversity and inclusion related industry surveys, RFPs, RFIs, and client diversity and inclusion related inquiries. Work alongside the department director to collect, quantify and benchmark data, trends and other related information, including the creation of reports. Identify and research innovative workshops and facilitators related to inclusion, talent management and leadership. Support the Diversity Committee, including scheduling meetings, distributing agendas, preparing meeting materials, and taking and distributing meeting minutes. Work with the firm's Marketing team to coordinate communication of the firm's diversity activities and initiatives on the firm's website and intranet; support the development of presentations, materials, and other projects. KNOWLEDGE, SKILLS & ABILITIES: Strong organizational skills. Ability to identify and solve problems, work independently, and take initiative. Excellent attention to detail. Strong team orientation. Ability to compile, review and determine logical conclusions or recommendations based on data and information which is varied in content and format. Strong interpersonal skills to work effectively with people at all levels. Ability to bring to bring the right mix of confidence, tact and persistence to establish credibility with Ropes & Gray lawyers and professional staff. Ability to maintain strict confidentiality of the firm's internal and personnel affairs. EDUCATION, EXPERIENCE REQUIRED: Bachelor\u2019s or other undergraduate degree is required Minimum of four years of experience working in attorney talent, human resources, or a related field. Professional service firm experience strongly preferred. Excellent oral, written and interpersonal skills. Proven dedication to excellence in customer/client service. Prioritizes and multitasks for efficient and effective work production. Establishes and follows needed procedures. Understanding of and familiarity with the diverse practice areas within a large law firm a plus. Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications (Word, Outlook, Excel, PowerPoint) required. WORKING CONDITIONS: Normal office environment. Incumbent is expected to work the hours necessary to fulfill the responsibilities of the position. The above is intended to describe the general content of and requirements for the performance of this job. It is not to be construed as an exhaustive statement of essential functions, responsibilities or requirements. "
